[Claude]: Now I have a very clear picture. The `handleResourceRequest` method in `OpenApiInterceptor` is the key vulnerable method. It:
1. Takes `getPathInfo()` from HTTP request (line 181)
2. Checks `startsWith("/swagger-ui/")` (line 204, 225)
3. Strips the prefix with `substring("/swagger-ui/".length())` (line 246)
4. Prepends `"/META-INF/resources/webjars/swagger-ui/"` (line 247)
5. Passes directly to `ClasspathUtil.loadResource()` with no path canonicalization

This allows path traversal via `/swagger-ui/../../../WEB-INF/web.xml`. Let me now search for additional patterns in the broader codebase.

